  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>General</Type>
    <Text>This is an ideal hotel for families with children, whose daily entertainment includes world-famous acrobats, magicians and jugglers performing in circus acts. The Adventuredome Theme Park is a five-acre indoor park sure to delight adults and children alike. The hotel has over 100,000 square feet of gaming space. Pool facilities are on-site, and a shopping promenade offers 20 stores for your convenience. Banquet and meeting space is available, as are wedding chapel facilities. The hotel features the only recreational vehicle park with full hook-ups in Las Vegas. (0606/CH)</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>SurroundingArea</Type>
    <Text>The hotel is located on the world-famous Strip. Palace Station and Slots of Fun are adjacent hotels.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>RoomTypes</Type>
    <Text>The Tower Rooms are large, with ceiling borders and pleasant artwork. Each is furnished in bright circus-theme colors. Bathrooms are well maintained and well lit. Wheelchair accessible and non-smoking rooms are available.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>PropertyInformation</Type>
    <Text>The hotel complex is comprised of two twin 15-storey towers, one 29-storey tower, one 35-storey tower and five 3-storey buildings. There is an Adventuredome, Recreational Vehicle Park, and the famous Clown Marquee to greet you upon arrival at the property.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>DiningFacilities</Type>
    <Text>The hotel has 11 restaurants, snack bars and dining choices range from Mexican and Italian to American cuisine.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>Short</Type>
    <Text>The lobby is large, and newly renovated, providing guests with easy access to all areas of the property. Reception is to the left side of the lobby, while the right side leads to the casino and restaurants.</Text>
  </Description>
